{
  "texts": [
    "The purpose of USL is to automatically extract the features and learn the pattern from unlabeled training samples to benefit further data analysis.",
    "Typical applications of USL include clustering and dimensionality reduction.",
    "Clustering focuses on dividing the training samples into multiple disjoint clusters, where the samples in the same cluster are similar.",
    "For example, K-means [192] and Gaussian mixture model [193] are two popular clustering algorithms.",
    "The high-dimensional training samples can degrade the training efficiency of ML."
  ]
}